[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Troubleshooting Base64 issues**\n\nI'm tackling a NoClassDefFound error related to `java.util.Base64`. I think it might be best to encode outside and use a hardcoded Base64 string as a fallback instead. If I set up a `FallbackAction` callable to return a byte array using `Base64Converter`, I need to ensure that `Base64Converter` is properly loaded. Additionally, I'm considering how classes like `StatusLogger` and `LoaderUtil` fit into child-first loading. It's all about confirming that the necessary classes can communicate without conflicts!\n\n**Analyzing class loading issues**\n\nI’m considering the dependencies on other log4j-api classes and whether a child-loaded `LoaderUtil` can safely reference a parent-loaded `LowLevelLogUtil`. It seems like it can, but I have to be cautious about how I handle class loading, especially with `LoaderUtil.loadClass(\"javax.xml.bind.DatatypeConverter\")`. I need to set the Thread Context ClassLoader (TCCL) to a custom classloader and ensure that it's using child-first loading. It's a bit of a balancing act with class dependencies; I want to prevent issues later on!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_020667cd864997a8016a0d98efa28c819ebfd1cfd3489ad12f\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqDZkF1w3JxNJNm9Sp9vB3o7h82sQT5N3p033el4-wWbXdziRhthnKP_Eh-99Ae-WR94PxbTXMUN8c3H_OeVWhFwE-3_bIvOOv5YCkyyTIuzLrfJrcXRO_Oimr4ihV9S4wXDonFn5jInVa_caFyjfknAy8fx0YQkIooKR64ZEO6BrT5hqV4dfUuNRIFas_GeMlYLBWQ5WEiLdCgm4ogMvgWuVkoYM9VBmxF-1JGYTnrU-purUF2E6Jqz6vEPOyzFPq2JDSlSr34vQPyq57FMe8cFgW7as1CTogEYJKegXN-JRM0APaVaFRGp5pBmKZ_rCEtl8i41oS3uVE0uBZijQJnPyN-j_mPvcoY8_mSRBObj_0bUcNdtIisWWIF5Dv3wKC6PcoFGrt-9cIHNNk1awBWrkzqcDPaHgdaGm6wE_cesZeL1wrIYqJHHVksYg8MvnJk_4ADXS-1DRb9c_nNsxqVtAYqTcyp_jP1FRoaQ4jI7zkpZJ55zuf8Jy6hfvxeRE3jMGqxboJaW9lwLFXvZWWhl1iVMsLXUdyM23Zhj6PG8GFH8J8V_9kEYRigud-o-L_64PmbwR3_xAVyMZo3vXtLghJOmK6KeUE1A8pfMCvDcxw8Kp5X0M